HEADWORD: Cephalata
<hw>Ceph`a*la"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>kefalh`</grk> head.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large
division of Mollusca, including all except the bivalves; -- so called
because the head is distinctly developed. See <xex>Illustration</xex> in
Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

